@NODE WhatIs "What is Chat-O-Meter - © KiLLraVeN/MYSTiC"
                          - -----------------------.
                         |  What Is Chat-O-Meter?  |
                         `----------------------- -

   It  started out as a tool to keep track of the time you spent chatting
   with  your users and to be able to make a nice looking @{"bulletin" link BullExample} out of
   that  information.   But  things  have  changed, not only does it keep
   track  of  the  time  the sysop spends chatting, it also registers the
   time every user ever spent chatting with you, the sysop, in a separate
   data  file.   So  for every user there is information available on how
   long  s/he  chatted with you and how many times s/he chatted with you.

   Needless to say that it's also possible to create a full ANSI bulletin
   based upon the users' data file.

   At  the  end  of  every  chat  you  will  get  to see a banner holding
   information  about  your  latest  chat  and  accumulative  info  about
   previous  chats.   At  your  request,  it  can  also  show  the users'
   accumulated information.

   Together  with  Chat-O-Top  you  are  able  to  create a wide range of
   bulletins  from  the  data  gathered while you chat.  Examples of such
   bulletins are:

   · Top 10 of the longest chats ever.
   · Top xx of the users that have chatted the longest/sportest with you.
   · Top xx of the users that have chatted the most/least with you.

   How  will  this  affect  your  chats  you say?  Well, I think you will
   hardly  notice  a difference since the creation and/or updating of the
   data  files  is  done  in  a  most  efficient way with as less fuzz as
   possible.   Creation  of  the  Top Ten Longest Chats only takes upto 1
   second.

                                ** NOTICE **

   Chat-O-Meter  is  giftware,  this means that you can use it as much as
   you  like,  where  you like, dressed as you like and how you like, but
   YOU MAY NOT SELL IT IN ANY WAY!  Permission is granted for distribtion
   on AmiNet.

