@NODE WhatsNew "What's New - © KiLLraVeN/MYSTiC"
                           - --------------------.
                          |  New in version 2.2  |
                          `-------------------- -

   Again,  I  have  optimized the executable and I am sure it can be even
   more optimized, maybe in the future (and without startup-code).

   I  also rewrote the routine that would keep track of your daily chats,
   as a result it is much faster and more reliable.  Please note that the
   first  time  you  use  this  version  and  a  new bulletin needs to be
   generated  by  Chat-O-Meter (because of a new record) there might be a
   record of 0 seconds and 0 chats.  This will only last for a day.

   The  total  time  that  you've  used  chatting with your users used to
   displayed  in  hours,  minutes and seconds (such as:  2254:33:15), but
   because  it  lacked clearity on the long run, I've altered it a bit so
   it is now displayed in days, hours and minutes (i.e. 93d 11h 23m).

   And  also  new  in  the  version  is the arrival of Chat-O-Top, a neat
   little  thingy  that  is  able  to  create  several  very  interesting
   bulletins, among others:

   * Bulletin of total chatting times with the users
   * Bulletin of the number of chats with the users
   * Bulletin of the average time per chat with the users

   These  bulletins  can be sorted either from high to low or vice versa.
   It  is able to handle custom designs and has some other handy options.

   Please check out the guide to Chat-O-Top for more information.

                           - --------------------.
                          |  New in version 2.1  |
                          `-------------------- -

   Added  a  routine  to  keep  track of your daily chats.  At the end of
   every day (that is, when you start to chat for the first time on a new
   day)  it  will  calculate  your  total chatting time and if it's a new
   record it will be added at the bottom of the Chat-O-Meter bulletin.
   See supplied @{ "example." link BullExample }

   Also,  at the end of every chat, you will get to see the current score
   of today's chatting time.
   See supplied @{ "example." link ExitChatExample }

   And due to some optimising the executable has become smaller.

                           - --------------------.
                          |  New in version 2.0  |
                          `-------------------- -

   The  previous  version ( 1.2 ) was released over one year ago (October
   1993)  and  to tell you the truth, the coding was lousy and it was not
   that  sysop  friendly.   But  do  not  despair,  this version has been
   totally rewritten (from scratch!) and is much smarter and has got some
   nice new options.  Better forget all about the previous version (1.2).

   It  has  to  be  said  that I would have never created this version if
   Quartz  hadn't  asked  for  it  AND if Stezothetic hadn't made such an
   awesome logo.  It seems people use my tools after all :-)

   First  of  all,  the best improvement is that it is now able to detect
   wether you started or ended a chat.  So if you were a previous user of
   Chat-O-Meter,  the  times  of  deleting  the  old data file before you
   started another chat are over :) Lost carriers are no problem anymore.

   Another  *BIG* improvement is the @{"new layout" link BullExample}, done by Stezo (Stz).  It
   now  has  got a really great logo and nice colours.  You'll love it, I
   do!  Many thanks to Stezothetic for creating the logo!

   But  that's not all, another exciting new feature is the creation of a
   data  file  that  contains  data about chats and times from every user
   individually  (but  stored  in one single file).  I will also create a
   door/tool  that creates a nice bulletin out of that one.  If you think
   this  is nonsense, you are able to turn it off so no data file will be
   created.

   The  previous  version also did not set the ENV:  variable of AMi-X to
   the right value, so users that performed a 'who' saw that the user you
   were  chatting  with was 'using a door'.  This has been fixed.  But if
   you  liked  that 'feature' of Chat-O-Meter, it is still able to hide a
   chat. Privacy above all (nope, there is no PGP function :) ).

   That's it.  I hope you'll like it, it's one of those nice little doors
   that  makes  just  the  difference  between your board and your follow
   sysops' boards.
@ENDNODE

@NODE Features "Features of Chat-O-Meter - © KiLLraVeN/MYSTiC"
                      - ------------------------------.
                     |  Features of Chat-O-Meter 2.0  |
                     `------------------------------ -

   · Super  Location(tm),  place  the  executable wherever you want (ENV:
     will do just fine ;) ).

   · Incredible  Creation(tm),  the  Chat-O-Meter bulletin can be created
     anywhere  you  like it, there is no discrimination of directories at
     all!  A first in Ami-X land!  :)

   · Ultra  Cool  Layout(tm), thanks to the Great Stezothetic a fantastic
     layout accompanies this package.

   · Top Security(tm), prevent users from detecting you are chatting with
     someone (optionable, but comes free with the package as a bonus).

   · Speed  Creation(tm), you have never seen such fast creation/updating
     of the data files and the bulletin.

   · Space  Saver(tm),  miniscule  files to store the data.  Now you have
     more room for your public domain software :)
   
   · Big  Brother(tm), not only YOUR chats are recorded, a record is kept
     per  user  for  ultimate  security and reference.  Now you can proof
     with  whom  you  have  chatted.   A  wide  variety of reports can be
     generated about this subject (Chat-O-Top).

   · Banner  Baffler(tm), comes in the famous Ultra Cool Layout(tm) style
     and  tells  you  all  about  your  latest  chats  together  with the
     accumulated info from the user you've chatted with (so you can check
     if  you've  chatted too much with him/here this month, remember your
     quota!  :) ).
     
   · Artificial  Intelligence,  Chat-O-Meter is able to detect wether you
     want  to  have  yourself asked the question "Show Bulletin [Y/n]" or
     not when a user hits the Top Ten.

   · Spelling Checker, optionable removal of plural 's's (no, this is not
     a typo) from words like "mINS", "hOURS" and "sECS".

   · Once installed, you will never have to do any maintenance!
@ENDNODE

