@NODE Install "Installation of Chat-O-Meter - © KiLLraVeN/MYSTiC"
                      - -----------------------------.
                     |  How to install Chat-O-Meter  |
                     `----------------------------- -

   For the illiterate sysops among us:  smack the executable anywhere you
   like  but  it's  better you put it in DOORS:Chat-O-Meter/ because then
   you  will not have to mess with those nasty icons!  Drag those vicious
   icons  to  your  SYSCmd  directory  as  quick as you can.  After that,
   modify  your  STARTCHAT.TXT  and  ENDCHAT.TXT  so  that  CHAT_START is
   started  when you start a chat and END_CHAT is started when your END a
   chat.  Now, that wasn't too hard was it?  :-)

   And now, for those of you who like to read huge guides, here comes the
   verbose version of the above alinea.

   Step 1 - Place  the  executable any place on this earth.  The supplied
            icons  have  been setup to find it in DOORS:Chat-O-Meter, but
            if  you  don't  mind editing the icons, place it anywhere you
            like.   Please  be  aware of the fact that the Chat-O-Meter's
            data  files  will  be created in the same directory you place
            it.

            Note  to  other  programmers:  Haven't you guys ever heard of
            the  PROGDIR:   assign?   Come  on, hard coded paths in doors
            suck big time, it lacks knowledge of the system.

   Step 2 - Copy   the   two   supplied   icons,   "Chat_Start.info"  and
            "Chat_End.info" to your SYSCmd directory.

   Step 3 - For  Chat-O-Meter  to do its job, you will have to alter your
            STARTCHAT.TXT  and  ENDCHAT.TXT  file(s).  These files can be
            found  in  your  BBS:NODEx/  directory(-ies), as you probably
            know (well, did ya?).
            
            Make  sure  you  call the "Chat_Start" command when you start
            chatting and call the "End_Chat" command when exiting a chat.
            You  can do this with MCI commands.  Consult your Ami-Express
            manual on how to do this (nah nah :) ).

   Step 4 - We're  done  with  the  steps. For ultimate performance, make
            sure  to  check  out  the tooltypes described below, they can
            really make your day.
            
   Step 5 - Oops, sorry.

   Chat_Start.info
   ---------------
   STACK=10000          ; Should be enough.

   There  are  no more tooltypes for this icon.  Sorry, I promise to work
   on it :)
   
   Chat_End.info
   -------------
   CHAT_END             : This  is how Chat-O-Meter recognizes the end of
                          a chat. Make sure it is in the icon.

   BULLETIN=            : Use  this  tooltype  to set the name (including
                          path)  of  the  bulletin that Chat-O-Meter will
                          create.
                          (i.e. BULLETIN=BBS:Bulletins/Chat-O-Meter.TXT)

   DONT_ASK             : By  default, whenever a user enters the Top Ten
                          of  longest  chats  s/he  will be asked if s/he
                          wants  to see the updated Top Ten.  If you have
                          something  against  that, you can override this
                          question  with  this  tooltype,  it will NOT be
                          shown.

   DONT_TRUNC           : By  default  all plural 's'-es will be removed.
                          So  for  example:  1 hOURS  becomes 1 hOUR  and
                          1 sECS  becomes  1 sEC.  However,  if you think
                          that  ruins  the  bulletin (cosmetically),  you
                          can  override  it  by specifying this tooltype.

   QUIET                : If you are one of those quiet types, and do NOT
                          wish  to see that ugly banner after every chat,
                          quickly  use this tooltype to make sure it will
                          never happen (god forbid!) :-).

   NO_USERFILE          : As from version 2.0.3 a file is created holding
                          all  information  about your users' chats.  But
                          if  you  think  that  the  8 bytes per user are
                          taking  up  way  to much of your precious drive
                          space,  you  can stop the creation of this file
                          with  this  tooltype. 

   NO_DAY_RECORD        : And  if  it  isn't enough already, Chat-O-Meter
                          creates  another  file  of  20 bytes (ack) that
                          holds info about the time you've spent chatting
                          today  with  users  and  it  also harbours your
                          tODAY  rECORD.   Again,  for  you poor guys out
                          there  with  too  little  drive  space, you can
                          prevent the creation of this file by using this
                          tooltype.  Goodluck!  :)

   That are all tooltypes for this moment.  When you are done setting the
   tooltypes  you  are ready with the installation of Chat-O-Meter.  Have
   fun and chat your head off!  :-)
@ENDNODE

